@page
@model HealthcareSupport.CaseEvaluation.Pages.Account.LockedOutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Account locked";
}
@*
    Custom Razor view for /Account/LockedOut. Filesystem precedence
    overrides the stock AbpAccountPublicWeb RCL page so this view + its
    PageModel substitute for the stock pair. Layout mirrors the existing
    ResetPassword / ForgotPassword overrides.

    Behaviour: shows a plain-language "account locked" message picking
    the failed-attempts cause (the only path that reaches this redirect
    today; admin-locks would route differently if ever surfaced). The
    duration matches the configured lockout policy
    (CaseEvaluationSettingDefinitionProvider: 10 attempts / 1 hour).
    A precise unlock timestamp is intentionally omitted -- the framework
    redirect does not carry userId so we cannot look up the per-user
    LockoutEnd from AspNetUsers without an extra round-trip; the duration
    is enough for the user to know when to try again.
*@

<div class="account-card">
    <div class="account-content">

        <h1 class="text-center mt-4 mb-3">Account locked</h1>

        <p class="text-center mt-3" role="alert">
            Too many failed sign-in attempts. Try again in 1 hour.
        </p>

        <p class="text-center mt-2">
            If this wasn't you, contact the clinic.
        </p>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <p class="text-center">
            <a href="~/Account/Login">&larr; Back to sign-in</a>
        </p>

    </div>
</div>
